public abstract class ExpressionWithoutChildState extends ExpressionState
Base implementation for those states who cannot have any children. (e.g., RELAX: empty, null, etc. TREX: anyString, notAllowed, etc.) Note that this class does not prohibit children from different namespace. Those "foreign" elements are just ignored.
Author:
Kohsuke KAWAGUCHI
